Response to `textDocument/definition` should result in `Location` | `Location[]` | `null` (https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specification#goto-definition-request-leftwards_arrow_with_hook), and `Location` is defined as (https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specification#location):

```typescript
interface Location {
	uri: DocumentUri;
	range: Range;
}
```

So `uri` is a mandatory `DocumentUri`; however, this is what I'm sending and receiving from the server:

```typescript
LSP:  >>> textDocument/definition
LSP:  --> {
            'textDocument': {
            	'uri': 'file:///Users/kronuz/filename.java'
            },
            'position': {
              'line': 167,
              'character': 42
            }
          }
LSP:  <-- [
            {
              'range': {}
            }
          ]
```

So `[{'range': {}}]` is not a valid response.

